---
Syntax: quaff <potion>

Drinks a potion from your inventory, triggering the magical spells stored
within it. Potions hold up to three spell effects which are all released
simultaneously when quaffed. The potion is always consumed in the process.

The spell effects are cast at the potion's stored level, not your character
level. Higher-level potions produce stronger effects.

Examples:
  quaff healing   -- Drinks a healing potion.
  quaff red       -- Drinks a red-colored potion.

Restrictions:
  - The item must be in your inventory (carried, not worn).
  - The item must be of type POTION.
  - You cannot quaff scrolls, staves, or wands -- use recite or brandish.

See also: recite brandish inventory
